speech.p: Does my hon. Friend agree that local people see Travellers as outside the social norm? In my constituency, local Conservatives have claimed that there is to be a campsite in the area, when in fact no such site has ever been suggested. Travellers are guilty of real antisocial behaviour, but the actions of local Conservatives are an example of that being exploited for purely political gain. The fact that there are no Conservative Members on the Opposition Benches for this debate proves that they do not care about what is a real issue for all our people.
